  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to measure abdominal wall strength both preoperatively and
      postoperatively in patients undergoing ventral/incisional hernia repairs. The investigators
      hypothesize that abdominal wall strength is improved in hernia repairs that reapproximate the
      rectus musculature to the midline. Abdominal wall strength measurements would be obtained
      utilizing various abdominal strength testing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
